  "title": "Service Engineer (Chiller)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>In charge of performing routine maintenance and troubleshooting of chiller systems to ensure optimal performance and efficienc</li>\n  <li>In charge of diagnose mechanical, electrical, and control system issues and implement effective solutions</li>\n  <li>Responsible in executing commissioning processes for new chiller installations, ensuring systems are installed correctly and functioning as designed.</li>\n  <li>Responsible in providing exceptional customer service by addressing client inquiries and concerns regarding chiller operations and maintenance.</li>\n  <li>Taking charge of preparing and submiting detailed reports outlining service activities, findings, and recommendations for future improvements.</li>\n  <li>Available to respond to chiller breakdown calls during assigned standby shifts.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirement</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Min Diploma in Engineering and relevant</li>\n  <li>Min 3 years of experience in chiller maintenance, commissioning, or HVAC</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To submit your application, please apply online to <a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com </strong></a>or call +(65) <a href=\"tel:6513 5697\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>6513 5697</strong></a> for private and confidential discussion.</p>\n<p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p>\n<p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd<br>\nEA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
